Dr. Mehmet Muş
9753503563
1. Baskı
Change or Continuity?
https://imageserver.kitapyurdu.com/select.php?imageid=4822280&isWatermarked=true
2017-10-30
 21,60
Poverty, hunger and famine are the common problems of Sub-Saharan African countries.  International organizations, affluent countries and philanthropic institutions provide development aid to Sub-Saharan African countries in order to deal with these problems. Together with member states, the European Union is one of the largest providers of development assistance to Sub-Saharan African countries. This book examines the EU's relations with Sub-Saharan African countries with respect to development cooperation policy. It investigates the actors and instruments of the Union's development cooperation policy towards sub-Saharan Africa over the past decade. It provides a comprehensive analysis of recent changes in the EU development cooperation policy and explains the implications of these changes for Sub-Saharan African countries.
